  "summaries": [
    {"book":"Joshua","chapter":1,"summary":"After the death of Moses, the Lord commissions Joshua to lead Israel into the promised land, commanding courage and obedience to the law."},
    {"book":"Joshua","chapter":2,"summary":"Joshua sends two spies to Jericho; Rahab hides them and professes faith in the God of Israel, securing a promise of protection."},
    {"book":"Joshua","chapter":3,"summary":"Israel crosses the Jordan River on dry ground as the priests bearing the Ark stand in the riverbed and the waters are cut off."},
    {"book":"Joshua","chapter":4,"summary":"Twelve stones are taken from the Jordan as a memorial; Israel camps at Gilgal and the crossing magnifies Joshua before the people."},
    {"book":"Joshua","chapter":5,"summary":"Israel is circumcised at Gilgal, keeps the Passover, the manna ceases, and Joshua meets the captain of the Lord's host near Jericho."},
    {"book":"Joshua","chapter":6,"summary":"Israel marches around Jericho for seven days; on the seventh day the walls fall, the city is destroyed, and Rahab's family is saved."},
    {"book":"Joshua","chapter":7,"summary":"Israel is defeated at Ai because of Achan's sin in taking forbidden spoils from Jericho; Achan is discovered and executed."},
    {"book":"Joshua","chapter":8,"summary":"With God's direction, Israel ambushes and destroys Ai; Joshua builds an altar on Mount Ebal and reads the law to all Israel."},
    {"book":"Joshua","chapter":9,"summary":"The Gibeonites deceive Israel into making a peace treaty by pretending to be distant travelers; they are made servants when discovered."},
    {"book":"Joshua","chapter":10,"summary":"Five Amorite kings attack Gibeon; Joshua defeats them as the Lord sends hailstones and the sun and moon stand still over the battlefield."},
    {"book":"Joshua","chapter":11,"summary":"Joshua defeats a coalition of northern kings led by Jabin of Hazor, completing the major military campaigns of the conquest."},
    {"book":"Joshua","chapter":12,"summary":"A summary of thirty-one kings defeated by Moses east of the Jordan and Joshua west of the Jordan during the conquest of Canaan."},
    {"book":"Joshua","chapter":13,"summary":"God tells Joshua that much land remains unconquered and describes the territorial allotments for Reuben, Gad, and half-Manasseh east of Jordan."},
    {"book":"Joshua","chapter":14,"summary":"The land distribution at Gilgal begins; Caleb claims Hebron, testifying he wholly followed the Lord for forty-five years since Kadesh-barnea."},
    {"book":"Joshua","chapter":15,"summary":"The boundaries and cities of Judah's inheritance are described in detail, including Caleb's conquest of Hebron and Debir."},
    {"book":"Joshua","chapter":16,"summary":"The allotment for Ephraim is described; the Ephraimites fail to drive out the Canaanites dwelling in Gezer."},
    {"book":"Joshua","chapter":17,"summary":"The half-tribe of Manasseh receives its western allotment; Zelophehad's daughters claim their inheritance, and the tribe seeks more territory."},
    {"book":"Joshua","chapter":18,"summary":"The tabernacle is set up at Shiloh; the remaining seven tribes have their land surveyed and allotted by lot."},
    {"book":"Joshua","chapter":19,"summary":"The final tribal allotments are distributed to Simeon, Zebulun, Issachar, Asher, Naphtali, and Dan; Joshua receives Timnath-serah."},
    {"book":"Joshua","chapter":20,"summary":"Six cities of refuge are designated (three on each side of Jordan) to protect those who kill a person unintentionally."},
    {"book":"Joshua","chapter":21,"summary":"Forty-eight cities with pasture lands are given to the Levites from among the other tribes; God fulfills all His promises to Israel."},
    {"book":"Joshua","chapter":22,"summary":"The eastern tribes are dismissed; they build a memorial altar that nearly causes civil war until its peaceful purpose is explained."},
    {"book":"Joshua","chapter":23,"summary":"Joshua, old and near death, exhorts the leaders of Israel to be faithful to the Lord and warns against mixing with the nations."},
    {"book":"Joshua","chapter":24,"summary":"Joshua recounts God's mighty acts from Abraham to the conquest, challenges Israel to choose whom they will serve, and renews the covenant at Shechem."}
  ],
